-- Nigeria's Governor Sanusi Says Economy is Seen Growing by 7.85% in 2010
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-11-23T14:10:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/nigeria-s-governor-sanusi-says-economy-is-seen-growing-by-7-85-in-2010.html
Nigeria’s central bank expects
Africa’s second-largest economy to expand by 7.85 percent in
2010, Governor Lamido Sanusi told reporters in a conference
broadcast by Johannesburg-based CNBC Africa today.  Nigeria’s economy may grow 8.29 percent in the fourth
quarter, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  